Here’s a product-grade frontend vision for your AI-employee business platform — designed like a real corporate command center, not a dashboard toy. This is structured as a UX architecture + interface system + interaction model so it can be handed directly to designers or frontend engineers.

1) Core UX Philosophy

The interface must feel like:

Operating System for a Company

Not a SaaS panel.
Not a chatbot.
Not a task app.

Instead:

structured

hierarchical

real-time

decision-oriented

executive-level

User should feel like CEO walking into digital headquarters.

2) Primary Layout Structure
Left Sidebar → Departments
Top Bar → Global Controls
Center Canvas → Active Workspace
Right Panel → Agent Details
Bottom Bar → Activity Stream

Sidebar = Organization Tree

Hierarchical company structure:

Company
 ├ Finance Dept
 │   └ CFO Agent
 ├ Sales Dept
 │   └ Sales Agent
 ├ Ops Dept
 │   └ Ops Agent
 └ Marketing Dept
     └ Marketing Agent


Features:

collapse / expand org chart

drag to restructure departments

right-click → edit agent role

Top Bar = Executive Controls

Global command layer

Controls:

company performance score

alerts

approvals pending

revenue today

agent health indicator

global command box

Command Box Example:

“Increase sales this week”

System auto-delegates to agents.

Center Canvas = Dynamic Workspace

Changes based on selected context.

Modes:

Mode	Purpose
Command Mode	interact with company
Agent Mode	view specific agent
Department Mode	department analytics
Workflow Mode	process visualization
Strategy Mode	planning interface
Right Panel = Active Agent Inspector

Shows selected agent like employee profile.

Contains:

role

permissions

tasks

performance score

decision history

recent actions

budget authority

tools connected

Buttons:

pause agent

retrain agent

change authority

audit decisions

Bottom Activity Stream

Live feed like company CCTV:

Finance Agent generated invoice #402
Sales Agent closed deal $1,200
Ops Agent scheduled shipment
Marketing Agent launched campaign

3) Key Screens Required
Dashboard (Company Command Center)

Must show:

revenue graph

cost graph

profit margin

top risks

active tasks

department performance

agent alerts

Design style:
executive analytics terminal

Agent Control Panel

Shows all AI employees as cards:

Each card displays:

name

role

workload

success rate

status

Click → opens full agent profile.

Workflow Builder

Visual flow builder like automation software.

User can:

connect agents

set triggers

add conditions

set approvals

Example:

Lead captured → Sales Agent → Finance Agent → Ops Agent → Report

Task Delegation Interface

Human-style delegation:

Assign Task → choose department → choose agent → set deadline → set authority

Approval Center

Lists decisions waiting for user approval:

budget approval

contract approval

hiring approval

Strategy Room

Advanced planning panel:

growth scenarios

forecasts

recommendations

simulations

Feels like:
corporate war room dashboard.

4) Interaction Paradigm

The UI should support 3 control styles simultaneously

1 — Visual Control

Click buttons, charts, sliders.

2 — Conversational Control

Chat with company:

“Why did revenue drop?”

System explains with data.

3 — Command Control

Typed instructions:

“Reduce expenses by 10%”

Agents execute automatically.

